{
  "stem": "8842.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We'll just tell them that we're going to look for more family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At the end when we'll find them, we will come back to Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's what we did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we got the first train we could.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Instead of going towards Lithuania, we went actually further in to going west.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we wind up to be in Lodz, which is one of the largest cities in Poland, and we found really a lot of crowds already, people that were deliberated.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they started to try to look for each other's families.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a lot of committees of people that they try to send letters out, who and who is where, and you just put your name on so we could find each other.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My girlfriend-- my sister's father-in-law left us there and then he said, I'm going to look for my sister, because at this point when we got there, we found that my sister is alive too.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That she was also taken by the Russians also to work in a camp-- in another farm.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he went from place to place and he found her, and he brought her there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He brought her to us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the first time I met-- I saw her again after this whole ordeal with the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We found each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was without hair.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She had typhoid and to see each other all over again was probably the most beautiful moment of my life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the oldest of my sisters because the middle one was burned in the ghetto, and the little one was taken away with my mother.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we-- the two of us understood that this is it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's no-- nobody else left in my family.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
